(71371, 199244, 6493, 1, 'Capital Boom Bap', '', '2014-01-01 00:00:00', 2000, 19, 0, 2, '[阮泰瑞]\nCapital boombap   How you love that\n這叫摩  登的時代 效率掛帥\n乾淨的運轉靠著骯髒的手段\n電子聲響配上old school boombap\n\n它們說這是天龍的國度\n過  獎了我們實在太cool\n專常冷  處理魔術\n新人總是感到無助\n外  行的都叫它做  冷酷\n\n兔死狗烹的 辦公大樓日光燈\n卡夫卡的延伸  一個世紀後的加乘\n多少K的文學  像是新仇舊恨\n不得不佩服  我們離題的才能\n\n這裡沒有我\n只有公主病的饒舌歌手\n到處存在的場所  到處不存在的我\n嘻哈台版村上龍  扁平化的摸索\n講了這麼多難得有機會囉嗦\n\n\n[Dallas Waldo]\n\n613 (yeah) Oh Double Tee (that’s right) A-W-A, Peace to Cap-City (one love) Overseas we got markets to build (word) So out in Taipei I still sharpen my skills (你好) Until - I get green and copper roof (like what?) Like parliament hill\nYeah I be in the R.O.C. - eating rice & drinking tea But don’t think I ain’t missin 4-20 and all that stinky green\nWheeew (put it in the air) - the winters can be sinister But homie, I’m a rider (yeah), rail slider (uh huh)\nTail gripper a big air getter Cause on the ice rink sloppy puck flicker （haha)\nBut when the summer come it’s BBQs, patios and icy brews Honeys in bikinis oooh - yeah (Waldo) Gotta get that sweet ass, back to my pad Glebe Ave. Then treat her to some weed smoke, blunts on the Rideau - for sho\n\n\n[Drix]\ndrix verse : I walk on the macadam , tread the pavements On the boulevards , rush hours man it''s hard to pass you don''t get the movement of the crowd , and too many pretty girls disturb your focus and then peoples push you and you become tired of that ( breath sound ) come on breath and take a break let''s go out of this to eat a kebab and then become crazy to smoke a joint (breath sound) after smoking 2 or 3 times we feel relax we lie down , write some rhymes and try to rap on the beat after the weed effect ,\n\n we realise it''s too late only the grossery store is open so we collect the money cause prices are expensive and we need something to drink streets at night are different , tiny birds are eaten ( means it''s dangerous for innocent people) wolves ( crooks) are looking for some tourists and local people can smell the danger others people are partying : alcohol and drugs till morning comes the luckiest are playing latex in satin''s sheets ( latex is for condom so it means make love ) Paris by day , Paris by day , for me it''s just Paname (paris nickname) Come in my capital , here it''s hiphop everyday \n\n\n\n\n[Tom Batchelor]\nIma tell ya bout Manchester yep, yo ima tell you bout the city that I''m from Ima tell ya bout Manchester the North Capital...\nI was raised in an oasis with the stones and roses came from a new order which followed a joy division 24-hour party people, coke up their noses These bands gave us visions then Expanding our decisions A resurrection, isolation using shadow play. Take away the blues and have yourselves a happy Monday I''m simply red on any given Sunday Red devils til i die, u-n-i-t-e-d This charming Manchester The city of beats the city o ball Though ya gotta remember, your not 19 forever So much selection, so much variety So much affection, that''s tied to our society So much industry in the past factories Lets lock the smiths in and see were more like Morrissey Lets rock this shit just like were back in the Hacienda We truly hope this city''s never gonna end!\n\n\n\n\n\n[2ko]\nUh.. Beating haters critics i''m talking modern classic city full of bridges riding going picnics we got beauty ladies chilling with my niggies (Money 1st) singing Fela epics, dancing Afro music I''m reppin for my city, ya all visit check it, nature made it scenic, the city photogenic, so much paper in it, half of ya wont make it, sit of power logic, I''m screaming f** politics Now bad man in the villa mehn I rep for the federal, crossing Univ zones thugs in the area, Cultist, black axe, only God no saviour\nStreet is a military you gotta be a soldier so, don''t mess up! you mess up, niggers f** u up, chop you up like egusi soup (haha), I ain''t brag am talking what''s up, is you know what''s up follow me up and say... F for the federal. T for the terriroty and C for the Capital Abuja. Yeah.\n', '', 344, '', '', '', '', 'StreetVoice 街聲', 'TWS651450001', 1, 1, 0, '2014-01-28 17:12:17', '2015-03-12 14:04:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(71372, 5224, 6494, 1, '更好的去向', '', '2014-02-05 00:00:00', 2000, 19, 0, 5, '像海嘯\n一轉身失去了所有\n像一場午睡做的夢\n\n一個人的選舉\n孤獨的舉行\n選出自己照顧他自己\n\n怎麼說呢\n不是故意一個人\n\n但你也知道\n沒辦法的事總是沒辦法\n\n「說服自己」\n沒有比這更難的立場\n\n除了這裡如果還有\n更好的去向\n\n離開現在\n等待的是無限的等待\n\n關於未來\n我想我就不要再做夢\n\n就算我會忘記我曾這麼說\n\n只要我知道\n沒辦法的事總會有辦法\n', '', 307, '', '', '', '', 'StreetVoice 街聲', 'TWS651314001', 1, 1, 0, '2014-01-28 17:17:59', '2015-03-12 14:04:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
